---
// suite-layers — Chapter 091 Lesson 1, "Project overview" / Architecture section.
//
// The honeycomb shape made spatial: a fat integration base and a single thin
// Playwright layer above it. Width carries the metaphor — the e2e box is narrow
// and centered, the integration box is the wide base it rests on. The eye reads
// "one test on top, the seam underneath."
//
//   ┌──────── Playwright — pnpm test:e2e ────────┐   (narrow, on top)
//   │ the full Upgrade-to-Pro composition         │
//   │ [sign-in ▸ upgrade action ▸ Stripe ▸ …]     │
//   └──────────────────────┬──────────────────────┘
//                          │ covers the seam the composition relies on
//   ┌──────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────┐  (wide base)
//   │ Integration — pnpm test:integration                       │
//   │ the webhook route seam · per-test rollback                │
//   │ [Next.js handler · test Postgres · Stripe sig · Resend]   │
//   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
//
// Each box previews its constituent parts as a compact muted chip strip — the
// e2e box names the composition's stages, the integration box names the four
// things that meet at the seam (the bug-density layer). The chips are
// subordinate: small and muted, a visual roster, not explained here (lesson 2
// owns the harness internals).
//
// Built with <ArrowDiagram> (LeaderLine) because the boxes are multi-line custom
// HTML — a monospace command title, an under-label, and an internal chip strip —
// which D2/Mermaid plain-label boxes can't carry. The single arrow leaves the
// bottom of e2e and lands on the top of integration, so the layering reads as a
// dependency (the composition relies on the seam below). Arrows are positioned
// from document.body, so the wrapping <Figure> MUST be expandable={false}.
//
// Chrome is theme-aware (Starlight gray/white vars flip light/dark). The arrow
// uses a mid-tone slate that reads on either background. A margin:0 reset on
// every node defeats Starlight's injected prose margins inside the figure.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
import ArrowDiagram from '../../../figures/ArrowDiagram.astro';

// The composed money path the one Playwright test drives, in order.
const composition = [
	'sign-in',
	'upgrade action',
	'Stripe Checkout',
	'webhook',
	'UI poll',
];

// The four things that meet at the webhook seam — the bug-density layer.
const seam = [
	'Next.js handler',
	'test Postgres',
	'Stripe signature',
	'Resend',
];

const arrows = [
	{
		from: 'sl-e2e',
		to: 'sl-int',
		label: 'covers the seam the composition relies on',
		startSocket: 'bottom',
		endSocket: 'top',
		startSocketGravity: [0, 40],
		endSocketGravity: [0, -40],
		labelOffset: [0, 0],
	},
];
---

<Figure expandable={false}>
	<ArrowDiagram arrows={arrows}>
		<div class="sl not-content">
			{/* ── The single thin layer on top ── */}
			<div class="sl-box sl-box-e2e" id="sl-e2e">
				<span class="sl-title">Playwright — pnpm test:e2e</span>
				<span class="sl-under">the full Upgrade-to-Pro composition · production build · separate saas_e2e Postgres</span>
				<div class="sl-chips" aria-hidden="true">
					{
						composition.map((chip, i) => (
							<>
								{i > 0 && <span class="sl-chev">▸</span>}
								<span class="sl-chip">{chip}</span>
							</>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* ── The wide base: the seam where the bugs live ── */}
			<div class="sl-box sl-box-int" id="sl-int">
				<span class="sl-title">Integration — pnpm test:integration</span>
				<span class="sl-under">the webhook route seam · per-test transaction rollback</span>
				<div class="sl-chips" aria-hidden="true">
					{
						seam.map((chip, i) => (
							<>
								{i > 0 && <span class="sl-chev">·</span>}
								<span class="sl-chip">{chip}</span>
							</>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</ArrowDiagram>
	<Fragment slot="caption">
		The two layers and what each covers. Integration tests prove the webhook
		seam in isolation — the wide base where the bugs live; one Playwright test
		on top proves the whole money path composed.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.sl {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 64px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 18px 6px;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.sl-box {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 5px;
		padding: 13px 20px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The thin layer on top — narrow, so the width contrast reads as a pyramid. */
	.sl-box-e2e {
		width: min(30rem, 100%);
	}

	/* The wide base — the center of gravity. Heavier border draws the eye to it
	   as the bug-density layer; full available width vs. the narrow e2e box. */
	.sl-box-int {
		width: min(46rem, 100%);
		border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		border-width: 2px;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-accent, #3b82f6) 7%, var(--sl-color-bg, transparent));
	}

	.sl-title {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sl-under {
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The constituent-parts roster — subordinate: small, muted, single row. */
	.sl-chips {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 5px;
		margin: 7px 0 0;
	}

	.sl-chip {
		padding: 3px 9px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-6, #f1f5f9);
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sl-chev {
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		line-height: 1;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: both boxes go full-width; the pyramid contrast softens but
	   the stacking (e2e above integration) and the arrow between them still read. */
	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.sl {
			gap: 56px;
		}
		.sl-box-e2e,
		.sl-box-int {
			width: 100%;
		}
		.sl-chips {
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}
	}
</style>
